thread.title: Kenya's central bank to sell 5-year bond worth 15 bln shillings in July
thread.title_full: Kenya's central bank to sell 5-year bond worth 15 bln shillings in July | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: Kenya's central bank to sell 5-year bond worth 15 bln shillings in July
text:
NAIROBI, July 10 Kenya's central bank will sell a reopened five-year Treasury bond worth 15 billion shillings ($150 million) this month, and its proceeds will be used for budget support, it said on Friday.
The bank said the bond will be open to bids between July 9 and July 21, ahead of an auction on July 22.
At the last sale of a five-year bond in June, its weighted average yield rose to 13.193 percent from 11.576 percent previously. (Reporting by George Obulutsa ; Editing by Louise Ireland )
